{
  "text": "Profilin, instead, comprises a family of highly conserved proteins, which are present in all eukaryotic cells and are involved in processes related to cell motility [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The first allergenic profilin was described in birch pollen and was designated Bet v 2 [CITATION_3] . Profilin sensitization varies between 5% and 40% among allergic individuals and sensitization to Bet v 2 was observed in about 20% of patients allergic to birch pollen in different studies [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] .",
